The paper deals with the problem of maximizing information diffusion in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses the independent cascade model, which is a popular model for studying information diffusion in social networks and falls under the sub-category of social network analysis (cs.SNA). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for finding seed nodes, which falls under the sub-category of search and optimization (cs.SO). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, and cs.AI.
